  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potato</strong> to a heatproof bowl, then cover the bowl with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 6-8 min or until the potato is fork-tender</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1652182300721-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1652182300721-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1652182300721-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1652182300721-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1652182300721-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced chicken thigh</strong>, cook for 3-4 min or until starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1652182307312-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1652182307312-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1652182307312-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1652182307312-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1652182307312-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Once browned, add the <strong>diced onion </strong>and cook for a further 2-3 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add your <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> </span><strong>flour</strong>, then cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1652182310318-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1652182310318-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1652182310318-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1652182310318-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1652182310318-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>,<strong> chicken stock mix</strong>, <strong>garam masala</strong> and <strong>steamed potato</strong></p><p>Cook for 6-8 min or until everything is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the sauce has thickened to a curry-like consistency – this is your <strong>chicken curry</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1652182312905-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1652182312905-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1652182312905-x700.jpg",
